@description.name: @description
@description.body: A page is the way to add content to a {@link TabView}. Each page gets a button to switch to the page. Only one page is visible at a time.

@childControl.name: @childControl
@childControl.body: button {qx.ui.tabview.TabButton} tab button connected to the page
@childControl.description: tab button connected to the page

@param.name: @param
@param.body: label {String} Initial label of the tab

@param.name: @param
@param.body: icon {String} Initial icon of the tab

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Fired by {@link qx.ui.tabview.TabButton} if the close button is tapped.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: The label/caption/text of the Page's button.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Any URI String supported by qx.ui.basic.Image to display an icon in Page's button.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Indicates if the close button of a TabButton should be shown.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Allows the tab to be excluded from the display

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Tab Change Listener

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Fires an "close" event when the close button of the TabButton of the page is tapped.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: By default, widgets are added to this

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Returns the button used within this page. This method is used by the TabView to access the button.

@return.name: @return
@return.body: {qx.ui.form.RadioButton} The button associated with this page.
@return.description: The button associated with this page.
